main event: A sighting of unidentified flying objects over the city of Seattle, Washington was reported by multiple witnesses, including individuals from the 143rd National Guard Aircraft Control and Warning Squadron and the Seattle Air Route Traffic Control Center on August 22, 1949.
interesting points: The objects were observed to be circular in shape and estimated to be 75 to 100 feet in diameter with a depth of 10 to 15 feet.
They were reported to be shiny aluminum and reflected the sun's rays.
The estimated speed of the objects was around 500 to 600 miles per hour, and their altitude was approximately 10,000 to 12,000 feet.
Witnesses described the sound emitted by the objects as similar to that of a jet aircraft.
No exhaust trail was noted, and the objects were seen moving fast in a straight line from south to north.
sighted object: multiple silver disc-shaped objects estimated to be 75 to 100 feet in diameter
witnesses: 143rd National Guard Aircraft Control and Warning Squadron, Seattle Air Route Traffic Control Center
